Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["FindPerpendicular", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"7a0b9aad-289e-4237-9798-59c5784d44ad"],

Cell["\<\
FindPerpendicular[graph, line, point] returns InfraPoint[{foot, ...}] for the \
foot(s) of perpendicular from point to line, computed by Euclid I.12 (the \
isosceles base midpoint construction): for each pair {a, b} of line vertices \
equidistant from point, the midpoint of the line-arc between them is a \
candidate foot. Multi-valued; returns the union. Method -> \"Embedding\" \
returns line vertices ordered by Euclidean distance to the projection of \
coord(point) onto the affine line under the graph drawing.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"356cb256-8c4c-4012-bcd2-639821aff242"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"89abe047-d062-4a31-b91e-5571103e4fe7"],

Cell["Load the paclet before running the examples on this page.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"3035defe-c72c-4bc9-a330-eb0439189902"],

Cell["Needs[\"WolframInstitute`SyntheticInfrageometry`\"]", "Code",
 CellLabel->
  "In[144]:=",ExpressionUUID->"51bc8c68-93a4-489f-b316-c8cb8e441930"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Usage", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"d04ee35f-6132-47f2-a4be-8ebf3ebed220"],

Cell["\<\
Foot of perpendicular from vertex 5 onto the chord {1, 2, 3, 4} of \
CycleGraph[5] -- visualize line in blue, point in green, foot in red.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"74f7b4cb-666b-467c-92db-38c9af5274a0"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
With[{g = CycleGraph[5]}, InfraSceneHighlight[g, {InfraSegment[{{1, 2, 3, \
4}}] -> Blue, InfraPoint[{5}] -> Green, FindPerpendicular[g, {1, 2, 3, 4}, 5, \
All] -> Red}]]\
\>", "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[145]:=",ExpressionUUID->"9f3b3eb6-70bf-4e82-a574-b5c94804e8d3"],

